{
  "id" : 772,
  "songNumber" : 160,
  "title" : "THE SANDS HAVE BEEN WASHED",
  "language" : "english",
  "originalKey" : "D",
  "capo" : 0,
  "bpm" : 0,
  "timeSignature" : "4/4",
  "hashtags" : [ ],
  "sections" : [ {
    "type" : "verse",
    "label" : "VERSE 1",
    "lines" : [ {
      "text" : "The sands have been washed in the footprints",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 4
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Of the Stranger on Galilee's shore,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 7
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 29
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "And the voice that subdued the rough billows,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 8
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Will be heard in Judea no more.",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 8
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 26
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "But the path of that lone Galilean",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 8
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "With joy I will follow today.",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 5
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 25
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "And the toils of the road will seem nothing,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 8
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "When I get to the end of the way. (2)",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 7
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 29
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : ""
    }, {
      "text" : "There are so many hills to climb upward,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 10
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "I often am longing for rest,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 11
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 23
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "But He who appoints me my pathway,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 4
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Knows just what is needful and best.",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 19
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 31
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "I know in His Word He hath promised",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 2
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "That my strength, \"it shall be as my day\"",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 8
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 37
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "And the toils of the road will seem nothing,"
    }, {
      "text" : "When I get to the end of the way. (2)"
    }, {
      "text" : ""
    }, {
      "text" : "He loves me too well to forsake me",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 3
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Or give me one trial too much.",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 15
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 25
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "All His people have been dearly purchased,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 4
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "And Satan can never claim such.",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 14
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 26
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "By and by I shall see Him and praise Him,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 7
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "In the city of unending day.",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 7
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 24
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "And the toils of the road will seem nothing,"
    }, {
      "text" : "When I get to the end of the way. (2)"
    }, {
      "text" : ""
    }, {
      "text" : "When the last feeble step has been taken,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 9
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "And the gates of that city appear,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 8
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 29
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "And the beautiful songs of the angels",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 8
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Float out on my listening ear.",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 6
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 26
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "When all that now seems so mysterious",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 9
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Will be bright and as clear as the day,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 8
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 35
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Then the toils of the road will seem nothing,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 9
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "When I get to the end of the way. (2)"
    } ]
  } ]
}